df <- scale(select(userdata, matches('melfix|lelfix|switches'), -matches('task')))
colnames(df)
 [1] "melfixcnthierachy" "melfixcntmodel"    "melfixcnttext"     "lelfixcnthierachy" "lelfixcntmodel"   
 [6] "lelfixcnttext"     "melfixdurhierachy" "melfixdurmodel"    "melfixdurtext"     "lelfixdurhierachy"
[11] "lelfixdurmodel"    "lelfixdurtext"     "melswitches"       "lelswitches"       "melmswitches"     
[16] "lelmswitches"

plot(hc)

groups <- cutree(hc,k =3)

print(g1 <- groups[groups[,2] == 1,1])
[1]  1  2  3  4  9 10
print(g2 <- groups[groups[,2] == 2,1])

Significant test between groups


# Add computed columns to userdata

userdata <- userdata %>%
              mutate(learnability = SUS4 + SUS10,
                     usability = SUS1 + SUS2 + SUS3 + SUS5 + SUS6 + SUS7 + SUS8 + SUS9,
                     score = (melacc1 * ifelse(melconf1 == " h", 2, ifelse( melconf1 == " l", 1, 0)) +
                                melacc2 * ifelse(melconf2 == " h", 2, ifelse( melconf2 == " l", 1, 0)) +
                                lelacc1 * ifelse(lelconf1 == " h", 2, ifelse( lelconf1 == " l", 1, 0)) +
                                lelacc2 * ifelse(lelconf2 == " h", 2, ifelse( lelconf2 == " l", 1, 0)))/8*100,
                     conf = (ifelse(melconf1 == " h", 2, ifelse( melconf1 == " l", 1, 0)) +
                                ifelse(melconf2 == " h", 2, ifelse( melconf2 == " l", 1, 0)) +
                                ifelse(lelconf1 == " h", 2, ifelse( lelconf1 == " l", 1, 0)) +
                                ifelse(lelconf2 == " h", 2, ifelse( lelconf2 == " l", 1, 0)))/8*100)


group1 <- userdata %>%
  filter (ID %in% g1)

group2 <- userdata %>%
  filter (ID %in% g2)

# Test for eye fixation count difference between two groups
boxplot(rowSums(select(group1, matches('melfixcnt|lelfixcnt'), -matches('task'))),
        rowSums(select(group2, matches('melfixcnt|lelfixcnt'), -matches('task'))))


t.test(rowSums(select(group1, matches('melfixcnt|lelfixcnt'), -matches('task'))),
        rowSums(select(group2, matches('melfixcnt|lelfixcnt'), -matches('task'))))

    Welch Two Sample t-test

data:  rowSums(select(group1, matches("melfixcnt|lelfixcnt"), -matches("task"))) and rowSums(select(group2, matches("melfixcnt|lelfixcnt"), -matches("task")))
t = 3.001, df = 5.9441, p-value = 0.02425
alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
95 percent confidence interval:
  163.6858 1627.4809
sample estimates:
mean of x mean of y 
1497.7500  602.1667 
wilcox.test(rowSums(select(group1, matches('melfixcnt|lelfixcnt'), -matches('task'))),
        rowSums(select(group2, matches('melfixcnt|lelfixcnt'), -matches('task'))))

    Wilcoxon rank sum test

data:  rowSums(select(group1, matches("melfixcnt|lelfixcnt"), -matches("task"))) and rowSums(select(group2, matches("melfixcnt|lelfixcnt"), -matches("task")))
W = 22, p-value = 0.0381
alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
